        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Define the Annotation schema — a Pydantic model describing a piece of inline text metadata (font style, links, etc.) with character-level range. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Text annotation data model for document lines. \par \b Input\/ \:  None (standalone model). \par \b Output\/ \:  Pydantic BaseModel <computeroutput>Annotation</computeroutput> with start, end, name, value fields. \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(7): pydantic.BaseModel] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Annotation.start &lt;= Annotation.end for all valid annotations.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Annotation.name is always a non-empty string identifying the annotation type. \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why use Pydantic BaseModel instead of dataclass? A: Pydantic provides built-in JSON serialization, Field descriptions for OpenAPI schema generation, and FastAPI integration. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
